name: Brigham Young University
description: Brigham Young University (often referred to as BYU, or sometimes just the Y) is a private university located in Provo, Utah, United States. It is owned and operated by The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints (LDS Church), and is the largest religious university and third-largest private university in the U.S.
